snippet: Even in their defeat, the protesters, mostly college students, left with a new sense of political identity and a willingness to challenge the power holders in Beijing.
abstract: Hong Kong police disband last of protest camps as nearly three-month Umbrella Movement is ended; many protesters, as longest sustained political uprising on Chinese territory in decades comes to peaceful close, say they are leaving with strong sense of solidarity and belief they can challenge Beijing's authority in future.

byline.original: By CHRIS BUCKLEY and KEITH BRADSHER

lead_paragraph: Even in their defeat, the protesters, mostly college students, left with a new sense of political identity and a willingness to challenge the power holders in Beijing.

headline.main: Hong Kong Protesters Lose a Last Bastion, but Vow to Go On
headline.print_headline: Police Disband Protest Camp in Hong Kong
